Then again at the cashier who held me waiting for half of order to, after 5 minutes, ask me if I was waiting for a  bag... I had to remind her of my order a second time and that she had not given me half of it! And why is the low fat vinaigrette sweet? I miss having a Panera near work. Won't be going back to Potbelly.

What can I say? It's a Potbelly.  *But* if you like a good, kicking coffee milkshake for under $4, these guys let you bring a shot or two of espresso to add to their standard coffee shake.  (Ok, you've gotta buy the espresso too, but there are several good choices nearby.)  If you want to try it, my advice is to cool the espresso over ice first. (Unless you like your shake thin.)  Then drain off the ice and ask them to add it when they make the shake. Yum! Buzz!!  UPDATE (Feb. 2019): for the first time in over five years, the staff refused to add my espresso.    Down graded to two stars.
